{
  "texts": [
    "Workers' skill levels are described by the distribution function Υ(J).",
    "For analytical simplicity, we assume that Φ(I) ≥ Υ(I).",
    "7 For a level of the automation index I, a fraction Υ(I) of workers are perfectly substitutable by machines and earn wage w j = A.",
    "A fraction 1 -Υ(I) is not substitutable, but given that the remaining workers are suciently skilled, they are all eective substitutes for each other and earn wage w j = F L (K + Υ(I), 1 -Υ(I)).",
    "In contrast to our baseline model, this captures the concern that automation may make workers on the lower rungs of the skill distribution redundant, whereas workers who are able to perform at higher levels of skill may benet from automation."
  ]
}